Threat hunting: MITRE ATT&CK and Wazuh!

Threat hunting is a proactive and iterative practice to look for any sign of adversary-related activities in our digital environment. It’s a human-driven practice! We can’t rely 100% on tools and automated security solutions.

It’s a job of a human expert with the aid of good tools!

We may have a list of tools to help us have a better hunt, and #Wazuh is one of them. A free and open-source security monitoring for threat detection, integrity monitoring, incident response and compliance. [https://wazuh.com/]

Here is a good read by the hacker news that briefly explains how to use the Wazuh combined with MITRE ATT&CK to hunt threats as follows:

• MITRE ATT&CK
• The Wazuh unified XDR and SIEM platform
• Threat hunting with Wazuh
• Wazuh MITRE ATT&CK module
• Wazuh rules and decoders
• Security Configuration Assessment (SCA) module
• Integration with threat intelligence solutions
• File integrity monitoring
• Wazuh archives
